  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants to try when visiting Tarsus, Turkey? What should you try while you're there?",
  "response": "Tarsus, located in the Mersin province of Turkey, offers some delicious local cuisine. Here are some recommended restaurants and dishes to try:\n\nRestaurants:\n1. Kalender Sofras\u0131 - Known for traditional Turkish cuisine\n2. Tarsus Ev Yemekleri - Offers home-style local dishes\n3. Y\u00f6r\u00fck Sofras\u0131 - Specializes in regional Mersin and Tarsus cuisine\n\nDishes to try:\n1. \u00c7i\u011f K\u00f6fte - A local specialty of raw meatless bulgur balls\n2. Tantuni - A local street food made with thinly sliced meat\n3. Tepsi Kebab\u0131 - A regional meat dish baked in a tray\n4. Mersin-style stuffed mussels\n5. \u015ealgam Suyu - A local spicy turnip juice drink\n6. Various mezze (appetizer) plates\n7. Fresh seafood from the Mediterranean\n\nLocal specialties:\n- Tarsus-style kebabs\n- Regional desserts like k\u00fcnefe\n- Fresh produce and citrus fruits from the area\n\nRemember that Tarsus is known for its rich culinary traditions influenced by Mediterranean and Anatolian cuisines, so exploring local restaurants and street food is highly recommended.",
